---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const homeHref = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const privacyHref = `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}privacy/`;
---

<Layout title="Support - SaunaMind">
	<nav class="sm-nav">
		<a href={homeHref} class="sm-logo">
			<img src="/logo.png" alt="SaunaMind" width="40" height="40">
			<span class="sm-logo-text">SaunaMind</span>
		</a>
		<div class="sm-nav-links">
			<a class="sm-nav-link" href={homeHref}>Home</a>
			<a class="sm-nav-link" href={privacyHref}>Privacy</a>
		</div>
	</nav>

	<div class="doc-container">
		<h1>Support &amp; FAQ</h1>
		<p>Have questions about SaunaMind? Browse our frequently asked questions below or reach out directly.</p>
		<h2>Getting Started</h2>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">What is estimated core body temperature (eCBT)?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">Estimated core body temperature is a derived metric based on peer-reviewed physiological models. Instead of measuring actual core temperature, which requires invasive techniques, we estimate it based on sauna time, temperature, humidity, and individual physiology to indicate which zone you're in.</div></div>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">Why measure temperature instead of time?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">Two people in the same sauna for the same duration reach completely different core temperatures. Time is a guess. The peer-reviewed research measures temperature thresholds where benefits activate, so SaunaMind tracks your physiological response instead.</div></div>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">How long should I spend in each zone?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">This varies by individual and your goals. Most research suggests 10 to 20 minutes in the Deep Hormesis zone, 38.5 to 39.0°C, is optimal for cardiovascular and longevity benefits. Start shorter and increase gradually as acclimatization improves.</div></div>
		<h2>The Science</h2>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">What's the difference between the 5 zones?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer"><strong>Warm-Up:</strong> Body is waking to heat. Cardiovascular response begins.<br /><strong>Heat Adaptation:</strong> Plasma volume expands and sweating peaks.<br /><strong>HSP Activation:</strong> Heat shock proteins deploy for cellular repair.<br /><strong>Deep Hormesis:</strong> Growth hormone surges and longevity markers peak.<br /><strong>Caution:</strong> Benefits plateau and heat risk rises, so exit and cool down.</div></div>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">Is sauna safe for everyone?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">Most people tolerate sauna well, but some should consult a doctor first, including pregnant women, people with uncontrolled hypertension, recent heart surgery, or fever. Stay hydrated and listen to your body.</div></div>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">How often should I use a sauna?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">The Laukkanen longitudinal study found maximum cardiovascular benefit at 4 to 7 sessions per week. For most people, 2 to 3 sessions weekly is enough to see meaningful improvements while still allowing recovery.</div></div>
		<h2>Technical</h2>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">Is my data secure?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">Yes. We implement standard encryption and security practices. Your personal data is not shared with third parties without explicit consent. See the Privacy Policy for full details.</div></div>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">How do you estimate my personal eCBT?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">We use physics-based models trained on peer-reviewed data. Inputs include sauna temperature, humidity, session time, baseline fitness metrics, and acclimatization history. The result is an estimated core temperature trajectory.</div></div>
		<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">My zone estimate seems off. Why?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">Estimates improve as the system learns your physiology. Hydration, caffeine, recent exercise, and acclimatization all affect heat response. If estimates consistently seem inaccurate, contact support.</div></div>
		<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">I'm not seeing zone transitions. Is the app broken?<span class="faq-toggle">▼</span></div><div class="faq-answer">If you're new to sauna, it may take several sessions to reach higher zones. Start in a moderately hot sauna and gradually increase temperature and duration as your tolerance improves.</div></div>
		<div class="contact-box">
			<h3>Still have questions?</h3>
			<p>Send us a message and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.</p>
			<form name="support" method="POST" data-netlify="true" id="supportForm" class="contact-form">
				<input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="support" />
				<input type="text" name="email" placeholder="Your email" required class="contact-input" />
				<textarea name="message" placeholder="How can we help?" required rows="4" class="contact-input contact-textarea"></textarea>
				<button type="submit" class="sm-submit-btn">Send Message</button>
			</form>
			<div id="supportSuccess" style="display:none;">
				<p style="color:#E8956A; font-weight:600;">Message sent! We'll get back to you soon.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<script>
	document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach((item) => {
		item.addEventListener('click', function () {
			this.classList.toggle('open');
		});
	});

	var supportForm = document.getElementById('supportForm');
	if (supportForm) {
		supportForm.addEventListener('submit', async function(e) {
			e.preventDefault();
			var btn = this.querySelector('button');
			btn.textContent = 'Sending...';
			btn.disabled = true;
			try {
				var res = await fetch('/', {
					method: 'POST',
					headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' },
					body: new URLSearchParams(new FormData(this)).toString()
				});
				if (res.ok) {
					this.style.display = 'none';
					document.getElementById('supportSuccess').style.display = 'block';
				} else {
					btn.textContent = 'Try again';
					btn.disabled = false;
				}
			} catch(err) {
				btn.textContent = 'Try again';
				btn.disabled = false;
			}
		});
	}
</script>

<style>
  .doc-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 80px 48px;
  }

  .doc-container h1 {
    font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 7vw, 64px);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #eeeeee;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .doc-container > p:first-of-type {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #555555;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .doc-container h2 {
    font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 20px;
    color: #E8956A;
    margin-top: 44px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .doc-container h3 {
    font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: #eeeeee;
    margin-top: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .doc-container p {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #555555;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: #0e0e0e;
    border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .faq-item:hover { border-color: #1e1e1e; }

  .faq-question {
    font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #eeeeee;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .faq-toggle {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: #E8956A;
    transition: transform 0.3s;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .faq-item.open .faq-toggle { transform: rotate(180deg); }

  .faq-answer {
    display: none;
    margin-top: 14px;
    padding-top: 14px;
    border-top: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: #555555;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .faq-item.open .faq-answer { display: block; }

  .contact-box {
    background: #111111;
    border: 1px solid #1e1e1e;
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 40px 36px;
    margin-top: 48px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .contact-box h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 900;
    font-size: 24px;
    color: #eeeeee;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .contact-box p { margin-bottom: 24px; }

  .contact-link {
    display: inline-block;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .contact-form {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    max-width: 400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .contact-input {
    background: #0a0a0a;
    border: 1px solid #222;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    color: #eee;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: inherit;
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .contact-input:focus { border-color: #E8956A; }

  .contact-textarea { resize: vertical; min-height: 100px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .doc-container { padding: 60px 20px; }
  }
</style>
